He's a handsome knight in shining armor.

815
00:56:51,407 --> 00:56:54,177
His chivalry makes me beam.

816
00:56:54,210 --> 00:56:56,946
But another father steps in.

817
00:56:56,980 --> 00:56:59,516
And another day gone by.

818
00:56:59,549 --> 00:57:01,518
And the months turn to years.

819
00:57:01,551 --> 00:57:04,320
More heartache builds up inside.

820
00:57:04,354 --> 00:57:05,789
But that handsome knight in shining

821
00:57:05,822 --> 00:57:07,690
armor-- he's gonna come riding up one day.

822
00:57:07,724 --> 00:57:11,194
And he's gonna rescue me from a father figure that

823
00:57:11,227 --> 00:57:14,397
brings me nothing but misery.

824
00:57:14,430 --> 00:57:19,002
One day, my fantasy father stepped in.

825
00:57:19,035 --> 00:57:22,939
All I could ask him was where have you been?

826
00:57:22,972 --> 00:57:27,777
15 years old and coming face to face

827
00:57:27,811 --> 00:57:30,213
with a father who'd been nothing but the family disgrace.

828
00:57:32,882 --> 00:57:42,125
Should I hug him, kiss him, run from him, or say I love you?

829
00:57:44,994 --> 00:57:48,631
Now the pain of meeting the real you-- you're

830
00:57:48,665 --> 00:57:50,633
no handsome knight in shining armor,

831
00:57:50,667 --> 00:57:54,571
just a pitiful, self indulgent fool.

832
00:57:54,604 --> 00:57:57,140
Go away, Dad.

833
00:57:57,173 --> 00:58:02,412
Please, please, please go away.

834
00:58:02,445 --> 00:58:05,715
Come back little fantasy.

835
00:58:05,748 --> 00:58:07,283
I want to live my yesterday.

836
00:58:23,333 --> 00:58:24,634
[LAUGHTER]

837
00:58:24,667 --> 00:58:26,236
CATHY: We should've put her birthday present on.

838
00:58:35,044 --> 00:58:35,912
Guys--

839
00:58:35,945 --> 00:58:36,713
DAN: What's wrong?

840
00:58:36,746 --> 00:58:37,847
CATHY: I don't know.

841
00:58:37,881 --> 00:58:43,186
I don't know-- oh no, oh-- no, no, no.

842
00:58:43,219 --> 00:58:46,890
Annie, Annie, Annie, Annie--

843
00:58:46,923 --> 00:58:49,192
[SCREAMING]

844
00:58:49,225 --> 00:58:50,326
CATHY: Why is this happening?

845
00:58:50,360 --> 00:58:51,194
Why is this--

846
00:58:51,227 --> 00:58:56,165
[SCREAMING]

847
00:58:56,199 --> 00:58:59,202
[MUSIC PLAYING]

848
00:59:37,674 --> 00:59:38,841
What's up, Dan?

849
00:59:38,875 --> 00:59:41,344
Hey, man.

850
00:59:41,377 --> 00:59:44,213
Yo, Dan, where you going?

851
00:59:44,247 --> 00:59:47,684
Yo Dan-- Dan, wait up.

852
00:59:47,717 --> 00:59:52,355
Dan-- Dan--

853
00:59:52,388 --> 00:59:53,256
Dan--

854
00:59:53,289 --> 00:59:54,223
Dan--

855
00:59:54,257 --> 00:59:55,425
-Danny-- -Norman--

856
00:59:55,458 --> 00:59:56,392
Dan--

857
00:59:56,426 --> 00:59:58,962
Norman--

858
00:59:58,995 --> 01:00:00,129
Wait up.

859
01:00:00,163 --> 01:00:01,197
What's wrong, man?

860
01:00:01,230 --> 01:00:02,699
You're not even hanging out with us anymore.

861
01:00:02,732 --> 01:00:04,701
-I've been busy. -Busy?

862
01:00:04,734 --> 01:00:07,503
You've been busy for the past two months.

863
01:00:07,537 --> 01:00:09,305
Dan, what's wrong?

864
01:00:09,339 --> 01:00:10,440
I want to work.

865
01:00:10,473 --> 01:00:12,175
I want to do something with my life.

866
01:00:15,044 --> 01:00:16,379
Life?

867
01:00:16,412 --> 01:00:17,480
We're just kids, Dan.

868
01:00:17,513 --> 01:00:18,414
Don't be so serious.

869
01:00:22,051 --> 01:00:26,089
I just want to do something with the future.

870
01:00:26,122 --> 01:00:31,661
All work and no play makes Dan a dull boy.

871
01:00:31,694 --> 01:00:33,329
I'm a man.

872
01:00:33,363 --> 01:00:35,665
Sorry-- make Dan a dull man.

873
01:00:37,500 --> 01:00:44,741
Look I just-- I wanna be somebody, somebody important,

874
01:00:44,907 --> 01:00:48,745
you know, somebody that my-- you know,

875
01:00:48,778 --> 01:00:51,547
that people will be proud of.

876
01:00:51,581 --> 01:00:53,216
I don't wanna end up like Annie.

877
01:00:53,249 --> 01:00:54,083
Come on, man.

878
01:00:54,117 --> 01:00:55,618
Annie's death was not your fault.

879
01:00:55,651 --> 01:00:57,186
There's nothing you can do to change that.

880
01:00:57,220 --> 01:01:00,523
And there's nothing you can do to change the world.

881
01:01:00,556 --> 01:01:03,659
Yeah, but I can change myself.

882
01:01:03,693 --> 01:01:05,028
And that's what I'm gonna do.

883
01:01:08,731 --> 01:01:12,235
I don't know what's gotten into you, Dan.

884
01:01:12,268 --> 01:01:14,637
I gotta go.

885
01:01:14,671 --> 01:01:17,140
NORMAN: Well, I'll catch you later, man.

886
01:01:20,743 --> 01:01:22,311
DAN (VOICEOVER): We were never a church

887
01:01:22,345 --> 01:01:25,281
going family-- full of weak-minded hypocrites,

888
01:01:25,314 --> 01:01:27,083
you said.

889
01:01:27,116 --> 01:01:30,853
But Mom somehow managed to sneak off to Sunday service.

890
01:01:30,887 --> 01:01:35,892
She never stopped praying for you or for me.

891
01:01:35,925 --> 01:01:37,660
Those prayers finally took hold, and I

892
01:01:37,693 --> 01:01:40,363
went to meet with the pastor.

893
01:01:40,396 --> 01:01:44,267
They were no hypocrites, Dad-- just people like you and me

894
01:01:44,300 --> 01:01:46,569
trying to find their way.

895
01:01:46,602 --> 01:01:50,973
And I learned there was someone who loved me unconditionally,

896
01:01:51,007 --> 01:01:55,878
who gave his life for me and would always be there for me.

897
01:01:59,048 --> 01:02:00,783
I knew it was time to make a change.

898
01:02:21,003 --> 01:02:24,407
Dearest Mom, wile growing up, it was

899
01:02:24,440 --> 01:02:29,078
very difficult to understand and appreciate all you did for me.

900
01:02:29,112 --> 01:02:32,482
It's only now as an adult that I am able to reflect back

901
01:02:32,515 --> 01:02:35,718
on my life and begin to understand the loving

902
01:02:35,751 --> 01:02:38,087
influence you had on me.

903
01:02:38,121 --> 01:02:41,657
Thank you for picking me up during the difficult years

904
01:02:41,691 --> 01:02:44,760
and for believing in me.

905
01:02:44,794 --> 01:02:46,829
It is only because of your unfailing,

906
01:02:46,863 --> 01:02:51,834
self-sacrificing love that I have become who I am.

907
01:02:56,239 --> 01:02:59,976
Without your encouragement, I would be nowhere.

908
01:03:00,009 --> 01:03:03,679
Without your prayers, I dread the thought.

909
01:03:03,713 --> 01:03:08,484
Train up a child in the way he should go, and when he is old,

910
01:03:08,518 --> 01:03:10,920
he will not turn from it.

911
01:03:10,953 --> 01:03:13,589
I see your face whenever I read that verse.

912
01:03:13,623 --> 01:03:18,728
And I pray that someday, I can give my child the same gifts

913
01:03:18,761 --> 01:03:20,897
you have given me.

914
01:03:20,930 --> 01:03:23,866
Happy Mother's Day-- your son Dan.

915
01:03:37,113 --> 01:03:38,080
[GROAN]

916
01:03:38,114 --> 01:03:43,186
[LAUGHTER]

917
01:03:43,219 --> 01:03:46,656
Woo-- huh, looks a lot better now that we own it.

918
01:03:46,689 --> 01:03:48,191
Sure does.

919
01:03:48,224 --> 01:03:49,192
Oh--

920
01:03:49,225 --> 01:03:52,895
Ah, well, we don't need this thing anymore.

921
01:04:05,841 --> 01:04:07,944
You've taken on quite a responsibility.

922
01:04:07,977 --> 01:04:09,712
It's quite a project.

923
01:04:09,745 --> 01:04:11,147
I'm ready for it.

924
01:04:11,180 --> 01:04:15,051
A lot of sacrifice for a young man.

925
01:04:15,084 --> 01:04:20,089
I know, but I want to do it.

926
01:04:20,122 --> 01:04:22,925
I'm very proud of you.

927
01:04:22,959 --> 01:04:24,126
Thanks, Mom.

928
01:04:48,251 --> 01:04:49,118
Yeah?

929
01:04:49,151 --> 01:04:52,855
Hi, I'm Dan, the new landlord.

930
01:04:52,888 --> 01:04:54,824
You mean you're the landlord's son.

931
01:04:54,857 --> 01:04:57,860
Nope, I'm the landlord.

932
01:04:57,894 --> 01:04:59,428
Yeah, well, you're a kid.

933
01:04:59,462 --> 01:05:00,529
You're the landlord?

934
01:05:00,563 --> 01:05:04,100
Uh, I know, but, uh, I'm him.

935
01:05:04,133 --> 01:05:07,470
Uh, so what seems to be the problem?

936
01:05:07,503 --> 01:05:08,971
The problem?

937
01:05:09,005 --> 01:05:11,941
Well, everything-- the, uh, roof leaks.

938
01:05:11,974 --> 01:05:13,276
The ceiling is caving in.

939
01:05:13,309 --> 01:05:14,844
That faucet in the kitchen keeps me awake all night.

940
01:05:14,877 --> 01:05:19,181
And the heat only works when it wants to, usually if it's hot.

941
01:05:19,215 --> 01:05:20,683
Wow.

942
01:05:20,716 --> 01:05:22,685
Looks like I better get started.

943
01:05:22,718 --> 01:05:25,554
Um, can I come in?

944
01:05:28,524 --> 01:05:29,525
Be my guest.

945
01:05:29,558 --> 01:05:30,593
Excuse me.

946
01:05:30,626 --> 01:05:32,795
So, um, where's the leak at?

947
01:05:32,828 --> 01:05:34,263
Kitchen.

948
01:05:34,297 --> 01:05:35,197
Kitchen.

949
01:05:47,777 --> 01:05:50,579
DAN (VOICEOVER): When I was a child, I spoke like a child.

950
01:05:50,613 --> 01:05:56,952
I-- understood like a child.

951
01:05:56,986 --> 01:05:59,021
I thought like a child.

952
01:06:04,193 --> 01:06:09,265
When I became a man, I put away my childish things.

953
01:06:17,506 --> 01:06:20,509
[MUSIC PLAYING]

954
01:06:46,035 --> 01:06:48,571
Hey, bud.

955
01:06:48,604 --> 01:06:49,505
Hey, Dad.

956
01:06:52,074 --> 01:06:54,043
How you doing?

957
01:06:54,076 --> 01:06:56,479
Good-- you?

958
01:06:56,512 --> 01:06:57,413
Fine.

959
01:07:00,816 --> 01:07:04,987
So, what's this letter about?

960
01:07:05,020 --> 01:07:06,455
Didn't you read it?

961
01:07:06,489 --> 01:07:09,091
Look, I'm not the cause for your messed up family life.

962
01:07:09,125 --> 01:07:10,459
Your mother is.

963
01:07:10,493 --> 01:07:13,095
Looks like nothing has changed in 18 years, has it?

964
01:07:13,129 --> 01:07:14,430
What's that supposed to mean?

965
01:07:14,463 --> 01:07:16,732
You're still blaming other people for your problems.

966
01:07:16,766 --> 01:07:18,667
She divorced me, remember?

967
01:07:18,701 --> 01:07:19,935
I wanted my family.

968
01:07:19,969 --> 01:07:22,238
I wanted things to stay the way they were.

969
01:07:25,441 --> 01:07:27,943
You know, when I was a kid, all I

970
01:07:27,977 --> 01:07:33,015
ever wanted was to grow up to be just like my dad, my hero.

971
01:07:33,048 --> 01:07:35,151
You should be proud to be like me.

972
01:07:35,184 --> 01:07:38,721
Proud of what-- being bitter over my past?

973
01:07:38,754 --> 01:07:40,022
I'm not bitter.

974
01:07:40,055 --> 01:07:42,057
That's exactly what you are.

975
01:07:42,091 --> 01:07:44,260
Look, I know, because I'm just like you.

976
01:07:44,293 --> 01:07:46,529
I used to be angry with you, but as you get older,

977
01:07:46,562 --> 01:07:48,197
the anger just turns to bitterness.

978
01:07:48,230 --> 01:07:51,167
Look, I worked every day to support you and your mother.

979
01:07:51,200 --> 01:07:52,902
I built a house for you both to live in

980
01:07:52,935 --> 01:07:55,271
and taught you all the skills to make a good living.

981
01:07:55,304 --> 01:07:56,439
And what did I get out it?

982
01:07:56,472 --> 01:07:59,975
What did I get, Dad-- a life of pain,

983
01:08:00,009 --> 01:08:02,945
and life of watching my father living with another family?

984
01:08:02,978 --> 01:08:04,380
She divorced me.

985
01:08:04,413 --> 01:08:05,314
No.

986
01:08:05,347 --> 01:08:07,183
You divorced her by failing to live up

987
01:08:07,216 --> 01:08:08,250
to your marriage commitments.

988
01:08:08,284 --> 01:08:10,085
She wanted to change me.

989
01:08:10,119 --> 01:08:11,921
No, Dad.

990
01:08:11,954 --> 01:08:13,589
No.

991
01:08:13,622 --> 01:08:16,959
She wanted you to love and respect her.

992
01:08:16,992 --> 01:08:18,461
Was that asking too much?

993
01:08:18,494 --> 01:08:20,830
She didn't know what she wanted.

994
01:08:20,863 --> 01:08:22,298
And what she had was never enough.

995
01:08:22,331 --> 01:08:24,600
That's why she divorced Tony.

996
01:08:24,633 --> 01:08:25,868
No.

997
01:08:25,901 --> 01:08:28,370
She divorced Tony because he was as abusive as you were.

998
01:08:28,404 --> 01:08:29,939
It was a tough time she went through

999
01:08:29,972 --> 01:08:31,340
after she divorced Tony.

1000
01:08:31,373 --> 01:08:33,442
That's what's-- that's what's causing all this pain.

1001
01:08:33,476 --> 01:08:35,911
He's caused the problem, not me.

1002
01:08:35,945 --> 01:08:38,447
Stop blaming other people.

1003
01:08:38,481 --> 01:08:41,317
Well, if your mother had run off with Tony,

1004
01:08:41,350 --> 01:08:42,852
we'd have still been together.

1005
01:08:42,885 --> 01:08:43,886
She didn't run off with Tony.

1006
01:08:43,919 --> 01:08:45,221
That's another lie.

1007
01:08:48,491 --> 01:08:50,960
What about all the nights I cried myself to sleep?

1008
01:08:50,993 --> 01:08:53,496
What about me?

1009
01:08:53,529 --> 01:08:56,866
You don't think I ever cried myself to sleep?

1010
01:08:56,899 --> 01:08:59,502
I have feelings too, you know.

1011
01:08:59,535 --> 01:09:03,539
After 13 years of marriage, a family, a house I

1012
01:09:03,572 --> 01:09:08,110
built with my own hands, what did I have to show for it?

1013
01:09:08,143 --> 01:09:09,411
Huh?

1014
01:09:09,445 --> 01:09:13,749
Nothing-- no house, no family, no marriage.

1015
01:09:13,782 --> 01:09:16,719
Well, you sure found another family quick.

1016
01:09:16,752 --> 01:09:19,188
And when you did, you forgot all about me.

1017
01:09:19,221 --> 01:09:21,390
I have a life too, you know.

1018
01:09:21,423 --> 01:09:23,392
Didn't I spend every other weekend with you

1019
01:09:23,425 --> 01:09:25,060
and send your mother child support?

1020
01:09:25,094 --> 01:09:28,197
Oh, that's real supportive.

1021
01:09:28,230 --> 01:09:29,665
You blamed my mother for the divorce

1022
01:09:29,698 --> 01:09:32,234
and made me suffer for your anger.

1023
01:09:32,268 --> 01:09:33,302
That's not true.

1024
01:09:33,335 --> 01:09:34,637
You make her out to be the enemy

1025
01:09:34,670 --> 01:09:36,405
then send me on like a wind up time

1026
01:09:36,438 --> 01:09:37,973
bomb to explode in her face.

1027
01:09:41,610 --> 01:09:45,915
You know what that does to a 9-year-old child?

1028
01:09:45,948 --> 01:09:47,883
I just got a divorce.

1029
01:09:47,917 --> 01:09:49,485
I was angry.

1030
01:09:49,518 --> 01:09:53,489
When you're angry, you just-- say things.

1031
01:09:53,522 --> 01:09:56,692
Look, I called you to tell you what I thought.

1032
01:09:56,725 --> 01:09:58,294
I was fighting to hold back the tears,

1033
01:09:58,327 --> 01:09:59,762
because boys aren't supposed to cry.

1034
01:09:59,795 --> 01:10:03,899
And I asked you why you never called me.

1035
01:10:03,933 --> 01:10:05,434
You remember that call?

1036
01:10:08,370 --> 01:10:09,438
Yeah, I remember.

1037
01:10:12,041 --> 01:10:15,177
Why didn't you ever call me?

1038
01:10:15,210 --> 01:10:20,082
Hey, I'm not a phone person.

1039
01:10:20,115 --> 01:10:22,518
And what was with that picture, huh?

1040
01:10:22,551 --> 01:10:24,286
That was the day I killed my son.

1041
01:10:26,922 --> 01:10:28,090
That was the way I felt.

1042
01:10:28,123 --> 01:10:29,892
Just because I didn't want you to put

1043
01:10:29,925 --> 01:10:31,160
your arms around my neck?

1044
01:10:31,193 --> 01:10:33,629
You backed away and said, what's with the arm?

1045
01:10:33,662 --> 01:10:36,098
I just don't like anybody to put their arms around my neck.

1046
01:10:36,131 --> 01:10:37,299
I'm not just anybody, Dad.

1047
01:10:37,333 --> 01:10:38,434
I'm your son.

1048
01:10:41,770 --> 01:10:43,038
I love you.

1049
01:10:47,176 --> 01:10:51,647
Don't you see what this is all about, Dad?

1050
01:10:51,680 --> 01:10:56,785
Loving each other, growing together as a family,

1051
01:10:56,819 --> 01:10:58,487
teaching your children right from wrong,

1052
01:10:58,520 --> 01:11:03,759
being there for them when they need you-- that's life, Dad.

1053
01:11:08,797 --> 01:11:11,000
What you want from me?

1054
01:11:11,033 --> 01:11:12,801
Your respect.

1055
01:11:12,835 --> 01:11:14,503
It's always been there.

1056
01:11:14,536 --> 01:11:18,741
I've never felt it.

1057
01:11:18,774 --> 01:11:21,310
I can only go by--by what you do and say.

1058
01:11:23,812 --> 01:11:25,581
Look, I can't live my life with bitterness.

1059
01:11:25,614 --> 01:11:27,549
I need to be free to love and to be loved.

1060
01:11:31,920 --> 01:11:35,557
I think it's time for me to hit the road.

1061
01:11:35,591 --> 01:11:37,860
OK.

1062
01:11:37,893 --> 01:11:39,995
Thanks for coming.

1063
01:11:40,029 --> 01:11:42,264
Mhm.

1064
01:11:42,298 --> 01:11:44,767
Look, I want you to understand that I

1065
01:11:44,800 --> 01:11:47,836
don't blame you for anything that's happened,

1066
01:11:47,870 --> 01:11:49,772
and that I love you.

1067
01:11:49,805 --> 01:11:52,007
And I forgive you.

1068
01:11:52,041 --> 01:11:53,809
And my door is always open.

1069
01:11:56,545 --> 01:11:59,982
Guess we don't have much in common.

1070
01:12:00,015 --> 01:12:03,252
We're related.

1071
01:12:03,285 --> 01:12:04,486
That we are.

1072
01:12:15,564 --> 01:12:18,500
My father, your old dad-- shaking hands

1073
01:12:18,534 --> 01:12:20,569
was always the manly thing to do.

1074
01:12:23,739 --> 01:12:27,042
He worked very hard, then he died.

1075
01:12:30,012 --> 01:12:30,846
That's life.

1076
01:12:35,818 --> 01:12:37,119
I gotta go, bud.

1077
01:12:40,055 --> 01:12:41,790
I love you, Dad.

